  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Upon Visiting Four Immortals Rock
  author: Seok Cheon-in
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The age of wandering immortals fades into distance,
    beautiful realms grow ever more serene.
    The clear stream flows blue as indigo dye,
    the moss upon the stones warmer than any cushioned seat.

    How brief these hours of wandering free—
    in a moment's bow and rise, the past returns.
    I would linger here without complaint,
    yet I fear the daylight slipping toward dusk.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: Four Immortals Rock (사선암) is a scenic Buddhist site in Korea, suggesting this is a meditation on impermanence at a sacred location
  - key: ''
    value: The poem employs traditional Buddhist and Daoist themes of transience, contrasting the timeless realm of immortals with the speaker's mortal awareness of time's passage
